data.name: Label15.Text
data.value:
1. Determine the starting player: Players can either choose who goes first or roll the dice to see who gets the highest number.
2. Roll the dice: The starting player rolls the three dice.
3. Score the roll: The player scores points based on the combination of numbers rolled. Here are the scoring combinations: - Lucky 7: If the player rolls a 7 (e.g., 1-1-5, 2-2-3, etc.), they score 7 points. - Three of a kind: If the player rolls three of the same number (e.g., 3-3-3), they score 5 points. - Run: If the player rolls three consecutive numbers (e.g., 1-2-3, 2-3-4, etc.), they score 4 points. - Pair: If the player rolls two of the same number (e.g., 2-2-5), they score 2 points.
4. Continue rolling: The player continues rolling the dice until they fail to score points.
5. Switch players: The next player rolls the dice and tries to score points.
6. Gameplay continues: Players take turns rolling the dice and scoring points until a predetermined score is reached (e.g., 100 points).
7. Win the game: The player with the highest score at the end of the game wins.
